## Risk & Compliance

| Change | Business Risk | Regulatory Angle | Act By |
|---|---|---|---|
| **[Exchange Server CVE-2026-42897 — June Security Update](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/released-june-2026-exchange-server-security-updates/ba-p/4524491)** | Unpatched Exchange servers can be exploited via a crafted email in Outlook Web Access, enabling arbitrary code execution. Applies to Exchange SE, 2019, and 2016 (ESU). | HIPAA (breach notification), CMMC (patch management), SOC 2 (vulnerability response), cyber insurance policy compliance | **Immediately** |
| **[Entra ID Security Updates — Legacy MFA and Custom Controls Retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-what-organizations-need-to/ba-p/4522024)** | Three legacy authentication mechanisms are being retired: custom MFA controls, Conditional Access during credential registration, and SSPR authentication method enforcement. Gaps in enforcement could allow authentication policy bypass. | NIST CSF (identity protection), SOC 2 (access controls), CMMC (MFA requirements), cyber insurance MFA attestation | **Plan within 30 days; enforcement timeline is end of 2026** |
| **[Exchange ActiveSync Certificate-Based Authentication Retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/retirement-of-direct-exchange-activesync-certificate-based/ba-p/4517896)** | Mobile devices and apps using direct certificate-based authentication to Exchange Online will stop working. New tenants are blocked today; existing tenants are blocked by end of 2026. | HIPAA (access controls for mobile health data), CMMC (authentication compliance) | **End of 2026; begin inventory now** |
| **[Legacy TLS Deprecation for POP3/IMAP4 in Exchange Online](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/deprecating-legacy-tls-and-endpoints-for-pop-and-imap-in/ba-p/4515201)** | Email clients using TLS 1.0/1.1 for POP or IMAP access to Exchange Online will lose connectivity. Primarily affects legacy email applications and service accounts. | HIPAA, CMMC, FedRAMP (encryption in transit standards), SOC 2 | **Confirm timeline; audit legacy clients now** |
| **[npm Supply Chain Attack — Red Hat Miasma Campaign](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/06/02/preinstall-persistence-inside-red-hat-npm-miasma-credential-stealing-campaign/)** | Over 90 compromised npm package versions stole credentials from CI/CD pipelines, cloud platforms, and developer machines. Relevant to any organization with software development teams using open-source package ecosystems. | SOC 2 (third-party risk), CMMC (supply chain risk management), NIST CSF (identify/protect) | **Immediately — direct your development teams to audit dependencies** |
| **[Microsoft Agent 365 — AI Agent Governance Now GA](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/05/01/microsoft-agent-365-now-generally-available-expands-capabilities-and-integrations/)** | As AI agents move into production workflows, ungoverned agents may access sensitive data, execute actions without audit trails, or create compliance gaps. Agent 365 provides the control plane to observe and govern agents. | SOC 2 (change management, access controls), GDPR (automated decision-making), HIPAA (access to PHI by automated systems) | **Plan within 30 days if AI agents are in production or planned** |
| **[Purview Data Security Posture Management (DSPM) for AI — GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-purview-blog/data-security-posture-management-for-ai/ba-p/4484148)** | Organizations deploying Copilot or custom AI agents without DSPM oversight risk data oversharing — AI can surface content that is over-permissioned or ungoverned at scale. | GDPR, state privacy laws (data minimization), HIPAA (minimum necessary access), SOC 2 | **Plan within 30 days for organizations actively using Copilot** |

