## Cost & Licensing

- **New Microsoft 365 Business with Copilot SKUs launch July 1.** Microsoft is introducing new small-business SKUs with Copilot built in, replacing standalone Copilot add-on purchases for qualifying plans. Organizations purchasing or renewing Microsoft 365 Business plans on or after July 1 should evaluate whether the bundled SKUs represent better value than current configurations. This may affect renewal negotiations in progress now.
- **Advanced Intune capabilities are being bundled into Microsoft 365 at scale.** Beginning in CY26 Q3, select Intune Suite advanced endpoint management capabilities will be added to qualifying Microsoft 365 plans. Tenants will receive 30-day Message Center notice before rollout. Organizations currently paying separately for Intune Suite add-ons should assess whether this changes their licensing cost structure.
- **Teams Premium license required for call queue recording.** The new automatic call queue recording and transcription feature requires a Teams Premium license. Organizations wanting to record contact center or support call queues automatically will need to confirm Teams Premium coverage for affected users.
- **Copilot Chat users now get Copilot Notebooks.** This expands a previously premium feature to a broader user base at no additional cost, increasing the value of existing Copilot Chat entitlements.
- **Exchange Server 2016/2019 ESU Period 2 is available through October 2026.** Organizations still running Exchange 2016 or 2019 that did not complete migration by April 2026 must enroll in the Period 2 Extended Security Update program to continue receiving security patches. This program has an associated cost and a hard end date.

*Sources: [Microsoft 365 Business with Copilot Announcement](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/blog/2026/05/28/introducing-microsoft-365-business-with-copilot-the-new-standard-for-small-business/) · [Microsoft 365 Adds Advanced Intune Solutions at Scale](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/microsoft-365-adds-advanced-microsoft-intune-solutions-at-scale/ba-p/4474272) · [Exchange ESU Period 2 Announcement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/announcing-period-2-exchange-2016-2019-extended-security-update/ba-p/4511603)*

